The source code in this repository represents the curriculum for my Practical Object-Oriented Design course (http://www.sandimetz.com/courses).

Anyone may:
1. Study it freely.

If you have taken the course from me, you may:
1. Share these examples with others who work in the organization that purchased the course.

You may not:
1. Use these examples in any public work, including blog posts, screen casts, and talks. You are free to study and learn from this code, but if you publish your ideas, please explain them using your own examples.

2. Create derivative works.

3. Use this content commercially.

4. Teach any course using these examples.
